The paper discusses the implementation of reactive distributed systems using distributed reactive programming, which involves both distributed computing (cs.DC) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also addresses issues related to coordination and partial failures, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a novel runtime for distributed reactive programming, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
